I'm really glad that you liked this movie. I will always be glad for every Star Wars movie ever made. Period. They make this world richer by adding to it something that wasn't there before, and my life would be so much poorer if they did not exist. That said, I had such a strong visceral dislike of this film. It had moments of brilliance that hit me emotionally but, in my opinion, did not come to fruition. All actors gave phenomenal performances and this movie will go down in history as making many fans happy a sparking new creators to expand the lore in the future.

I am just not one of those people. I am full of disappointment at the unfulfilled potential and missed opportunities that this film had, and it breaks my heart. I was looking forward to seeing this film many times, but at this point I don't even want to go back again once. I am truly happy that this film is joy to so many, I just wish it could be a joy for me.

I grew up on Star Wars. I vividly remember going to the theater when I was 6 years old to watch the final prequel movie, Revenge of the Sith. I then saw it 6 more times in the theater. I’ve very nostalgic towards Star Wars and it’s my favorite universe. I’ve read books, played games and really dived into the lore of it all. But the Disney trilogy has disappointed me.
The prequels told a story of how a young boy turns to the dark side of the force. You see Anakin’s journey and feel connected to his journey and the other characters around him like his friendship with Obi-wan and chancellor Palpatine. The original trilogy tells a story of how a farm boy wants more in life and has big aspirations and dreams that eventually get fulfilled. The story of Luke saving his father. His father had been a slave his whole life from being on the Jedi Order to being a slave to the emperor. Vader finally felt free when he saved his son because that’s finally when he got the power to save the ones he loved. The entire saga is about Anakin and fulling the “chosen one” prophecy of bringing balance to the force. You felt and knew the characters and the story that it told. Not with the Disney sequel trilogy.
The Disney sequel trilogy is a mess. It’s unoriginal. Episode 8 is at least somewhat original as described later. But, the trilogy didn’t know what story to tell or what they wanted for its characters. Episode 7 asks all these questions: how did maz get Luke’s lightsaber? Who is Rey? Why did Kylo turn to the dark side? Why does the first order exist? Episode 8 decides to answer these question by saying Kylo is a student to Luke who’s raw power scared Luke because it reminded him of his father. Rey is just a normal person who happens to be strong in the force. Whatever the first order actually is is being led by kylo and that snoke wasn’t an eveil dark sith after all. The republic is plagued with leadership problems and people like Poe and Finn think they can go off and save the day. It’s set up to say in the next movie how does Rey who has this new knowledge of what it means to be a true jedi defeat Kylo who is now a Sith Lord as he killed his own master to become it. Then episode 9 completely throws all this away. The first order is just Palpatines empire. Kylo wasn’t someone who became a Sith Lord himself, he was just a pawn of Palpatine. Rey wasn’t this independent force user who could learn this on her own, she was always a Skywalker destined to do all this as Anakin is palpatines son and Rey is palpatines granddaughter. It rehashes similar plot points but these movies didn’t know what they wanted to be. These movies couldn’t be their own movies and couldn’t follow one story. I at least respect episode 8 for trying to be different and stray away from the Skywalker saga we’ve already seen.

TLDR; my opinion is the Disney sequel trilogy sucks and will never surpass the original episodes 1-6.

snippet.textDisplay: I am so happy to see a genuine fan of the franchise love this movie. I thought it was awesome too and personally I also did not enjoy The Last Jedi as a Star Wars film connected to the Canon Star Wars lore. As just a film Last Jedi was good other than the god awful choreography but as a story connected film it felt forced (no pun intended) and Just felt like it was trying to sway against the breeze for no other reason than because it could. Then this film tried to salvage what so many fans felt was lost in the last movie. And it was slated by critics saying it tried to service the fans too much but the last film was slated for going against the fans at every turn. When can you win? I genuinely feel that if Abrams was just given the trilogy creatively then it would have been truly great for more people. But it wasn’t and this film had to follow The Last Jedi and that’s that. It tried to fix an armada of fans broken dreams from the last film and personally I felt it did but I can truly get how it didn’t for others. I can agree it’s too much crammed into 2 hours but Abrams couldn’t make it 2 films that wasn’t up to him so personally I felt he did the best he could. I really felt that Force Awakens mirrored a new hope, the Last Jedi mirrored Empire and this mirrored Return. There were elements all 3 did right but there were so many more elements episode 7 & 9 did better and they genuinely blended. The odd one out for me is 8 and that’s just my opinion but anyway for me a definite love for Rise of Skywalker and a merry Xmas to all! May the Force be with you, always!

snippet.textDisplay:
I feel like all of us fans pretty much got what we wanted out of these new films for the most part:

TFA = Familiarity

TLJ = Originality

TROS = Fanfiction

Ofc not everyone likes these decisions and you can’t please everyone. I like all three sequel films for different reasons and I honestly loved the last Jedi for some of the reasons you hated it for, which is totally fine! The thing with Luke disrespecting his dad’s weapon is Cos he wanted nothing to do with it. He’s had nothing but traumatic experiences and pain brought by that thing. So while we fans and audience members see that lightsaber as a special piece of history, the character itself doesn’t give a shit. At least until now. I also don’t think TLJ was negated at all. Luke’s acknowledgments are all rooted from TLJ.

But again that’s just me. I loved all three films. TROS was my least favorite, but I still don’t hate it at all. It’s got more pros than cons in my book.

snippet.textDisplay: We should have seen more force ghosts, Luke and Leia are not enough. We should have seen all the force ghosts including Ben Solo and Anakin. Anakin should have been in this movie far more than a few lines of dialogue, how can you make a movie called The rise of Skywalker and barely include Anakin?? I didnt like this movie because, despite it's name, it is not about the Skywalker family, rather the Palpatines. In fact the title doesn't make sense. it makes Anakin feel obsolete and unneccessary. It ruins the fact that Anakin is the chosen one, it ignores and replaces its main character. It really isn't the Skywalker saga anymore, that ended with 6. This is not what George would have wanted.
